==Russian==
[[Category:Russian nouns]]

Do not confuse with [[русский]] and [[российский]]/[[россиянин]], which both translated to English as [[Russian]].

Word [[русский]] concerning a person or people means pertaining to [[Russians]] as East Slavic ethnic group only, but not for all people of Russia.

Word [[российский]] means pertaining to Russia as [[state]], [[country]] and [[nation]] of Russia.

===Noun===
'''ру́сский''' (rússkij) {{m}}, русская (rússkaja) {{f}}, русские (rússkije) {{p}}
# [[Russian]], a Russian person (meaning of Russian ethnicity, not about people just living in Russia, see [[россиянин]])
#: ты что, не русский? — ''You are Russian, don't you?''
# {{colloquial}} the Russian [[language]]
#: ты знаешь русский? — ''Do you know Russian?''

'''Ру́сский''' (Rússkij) {{m}}, [[остров|о́стров]] Русский — Russian Island near [[Vladivostok]]

===Adjective===
'''ру́сский''' (rússkij) {{m}}

# Of or pertaining to [[Russia]] or the [[Russian]]s.
#: ру́сская [[водка|во́дка]] — ''Russian [[vodka]]''
#: ру́сская [[выхухоль|вы́хухоль]] — ''(Desmana moschata) Russian [[desman]], Russian [[muskrat]]''
#: ру́сский [[замок|замо́к]] — ''Russian [[lock]]'', ''Sklifosovsky's lock''
#: ру́сский [[осётр]] — ''(Acipenser gueldenstaedti) Russian [[sturgeon]]''
#: ру́сский [[мороз]] — ''russian frost'' (very cold weather)
# {{figurative}} Of a person, being from [[Russia]].
#: Русская Америка — ''Russian America'', meaning Russian-speaking people (not necessary belonging to Russian ethnic group) living in USA
#: ру́сский [[хоккей|хокке́й]] — ''Russian [[hockey]]''

